title: 2 Eleven on Signing to Jeezy, How It Went Wrong, Boskoe Beef & More
description:
2 Eleven tells T-Rell everything about his journey to become an entrepreneur, navigating the music industry, working with Jeezy and more!

-----
00:00 Intro
0:55 - How 2eleven and TF met at a G Perico party being Bloods & Crips
6:54 - Collab with Conway, meeting him on a Griselda tour, connecting with Larry June
10:34 - Being an entrepreneur, starting a store and only having 2 pairs of sneakers in it at first
15:08 - Being signed in 06-07 Streaming changing the game for independent artists
16:05 - Signed by Young Jeezy to CTE for $15k, falling out with him over $400k
20:35 - Being emotional over leaving CTE, having relationships ruined over Jeezy’s beefs
25:02 - T-Rell on seeing Ben Baller run from Suge Knight at a Lil Wayne concert
26:06 - 2eleven was on vacation when Suge Knight called him to the studio for a 2pac song
30:31 - Regretting being involved in viral Boskoe situation
40:38 - T-Rell rapping on TF song that never came out, 2eleven ask if he tried to rap with Tyga
43:50 - Wanting Mac10 to show more love to the artist in the city, wanting him to come outside
48:10 - Not playing industry games with other artists, taking artist off songs if their not fire
50:48 - 2eleven shouts out “Gina’s fine a**”, wanting to start a “Brofessions”
